Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.92,0:00:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\move(189.6,121.6,193.8,105.6,0,356)}{\b1\bord0\shad3\3c&H2F2F2F&\4c&H336D99&}{\fs10}{\t(0,356,\fs20)}前情提要
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.68,0:00:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反恐局的托尼·阿尔梅达刚刚通知我们\N{\r原文字幕}Tony Almeida from CTU has just informed us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.26,0:00:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们没法在墨西哥没收这个科迪利亚病毒\N{\r原文字幕}that they were unable to confiscate this Cordilla virus in Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.14,0:00:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个叫阿马多尔的人 他现在在哪?\N{\r原文字幕}This man Amador, where is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.22,0:00:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最新证据表明病毒在阿马多尔手上\N{\r原文字幕}Latest working theory is that Amador has this virus,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.03,0:00:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他正在回洛杉矶的路上\N{\r原文字幕}and is headed back here to Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.13,0:00:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我救了你一命 告诉我你知道些什么\N{\r原文字幕}I let you live. Tell me what you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.24,0:00:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每次阿马多尔在西海岸做交易的时候\N{\r原文字幕}Any time Amador does business on the west coast,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.79,0:00:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是通过一个叫阿尔弗斯的人\N{\r原文字幕}he washes his deal through a man named Alvers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.33,0:00:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿马多尔怎么和这个阿尔弗斯联系呢?\N{\r原文字幕}How does Amador contact this Alvers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道 我没见过他\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know. I've never met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.80,0:00:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喂?\N{\r原文字幕}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.85,0:00:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马库斯 是我\N{\r原文字幕}Marcus, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.31,0:00:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一个小时后到\N{\r原文字幕}I'll be there in an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.95,0:00:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿到病毒了吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Got the virus?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.88,0:00:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿到了\N{\r原文字幕}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.13,0:00:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做好准备\N{\r原文字幕}Just be ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会的\N{\r原文字幕}I will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.69,0:00:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去见朱莉娅 米利肯\N{\r原文字幕}I got to go see Julia Milliken.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.46,0:00:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不行 今晚你必须离她或是艾伦远远的\N{\r原文字幕}No. I don't want you to go anywhere near her or Alan tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.61,0:00:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为我怕你吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Do you think I'm scared of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.18,0:00:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,茱莉娅...\N{\r原文字幕}Julia...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.57,0:00:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的药\N{\r原文字幕}My pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.70,0:01:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 不要\N{\r原文字幕}No, don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.88,0:01:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你在干什么?  -不要\N{\r原文字幕}-What are you doing?  -Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.98,0:01:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-雪莉?  -这是你唯一的出路\N{\r原文字幕}-Sherry?  -This is your way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.65,0:01:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们杀了他  -不是\N{\r原文字幕}-We killed him.  -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.17,0:01:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有件事你必须要清楚\N{\r原文字幕}There's one thing you're going to have to be really clear about,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.50,0:01:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果有警察局的人来问话\N{\r原文字幕}when the authorities come around questioning you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.11,0:01:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就说我没有来过\N{\r原文字幕}I was never here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.61,0:01:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以下事件发生于凌晨两点至三点之间 均与现实同步\N{\r原文字幕}The following takes place between 2:00 a.m. and 3:00 a.m..
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.20,0:01:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,木谷尖端海军飞机场\N{\r原文字幕}Point Mugu Naval Air Station
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.62,0:02:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我抓到她了\N{\r原文字幕}I got her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.83,0:02:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-鲍尔探员  -我是\N{\r原文字幕}-Agent Bauer.  -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.17,0:02:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是分局的杰森·卡鲁松\N{\r原文字幕}I'm Jason Carusone from Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.43,0:02:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会把囚犯护送回反恐局\N{\r原文字幕}These men will be escorting the prisoner back to CTU.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.59,0:02:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她不能离开我的视线\N{\r原文字幕}She doesn't leave my sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.88,0:02:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道 你可以跟她一起坐领头车回去\N{\r原文字幕}I know. You can accompany her in the lead van.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.76,0:02:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走吧!\N{\r原文字幕}Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.94,0:02:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是卡鲁松\N{\r原文字幕}This is Carusone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 是的 他就在这里\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah. Yeah, he's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.93,0:02:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埃德蒙兹探员\N{\r原文字幕}Agent Edmunds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.51,0:02:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是你办公室的克萝伊·奥布莱恩\N{\r原文字幕}It's Chloe O'brian from your office.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.62,0:02:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 杰克 我坐另一辆车\N{\r原文字幕}Hey, Jack, I'll take another car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.38,0:02:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.48,0:02:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我 克萝伊?\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, Chloe?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.99,0:02:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蔡斯 他们知道了\N{\r原文字幕}Chase, they found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.21,0:02:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁知道了什么?\N{\r原文字幕}Who found out what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.42,0:02:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的每个人都知道了安吉拉\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody here found out about Angela.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.89,0:02:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都知道她是你女儿\N{\r原文字幕}They all know she's your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.78,0:02:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么? 他们怎么知道的?\N{\r原文字幕}What? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保姆走了 她家里有急事 就把她带到这里来了\N{\r原文字幕}The baby-sitter flaked. She had a family emergency and brought her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把安吉拉带到反恐局了?\N{\r原文字幕}You brought Angela into CTU?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.27,0:02:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还能怎么做?你姐姐出城了\N{\r原文字幕}What was I supposed to do? Your sister's out of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.09,0:02:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有别人了\N{\r原文字幕}There is no one else.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.21,0:02:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不知道我这几个小时是怎么过来的\N{\r原文字幕}You have no idea what I've been through in the past couple of hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.71,0:02:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好 好 好\N{\r原文字幕}Okay, okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.09,0:02:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克萝伊 谢谢你帮我处理\N{\r原文字幕}Chloe, thank you for covering.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.54,0:02:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常感谢 但是安吉拉现在在哪?\N{\r原文字幕}I appreciate it. But where is Angela right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.15,0:02:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她和马尔西在楼下等你回来\N{\r原文字幕}She's downstairs with Marcy until you get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.19,0:02:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金知道了吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Did Kim find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.90,0:03:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克萝伊 金知道了没有?\N{\r原文字幕}Chloe, did Kim find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.04,0:03:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 是的 金知道了\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, yes, Kim found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.52,0:03:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她什么反应?\N{\r原文字幕}How did she react?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.02,0:03:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 天哪 蔡斯 我想她有点生气\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, Gosh, Chase, I think she's kind of pissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.50,0:03:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 听我说 我马上就回反恐局\N{\r原文字幕}All right, listen. I'm coming back to CTU right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.42,0:03:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会处理好一切的\N{\r原文字幕}I'll take care of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.55,0:03:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\r原文字幕}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.36,0:03:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,情况是这样的:\N{\r原文字幕}Here's the situation:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.63,0:03:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为迈克尔 阿马多尔拿了科迪利亚病毒\N{\r原文字幕}we believe Michael Amador is in possession of the Cordilla virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.16,0:03:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他应该正往洛杉矶赶来 或许已经到了\N{\r原文字幕}We believe he is either headed to Los Angeles or he's here already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.70,0:03:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们估计他有足够的病毒 能摧毁一整个大都市\N{\r原文字幕}We estimate he has enough of the pathogen to take out a major metropolitan area.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.45,0:03:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们唯一的线索就是尼娜·迈尔斯 她正在被带回来的路上\N{\r原文字幕}Our only lead is Nina Myers, who's being brought back to CTU right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.13,0:03:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她认为阿马多尔正赶来洛杉矶同一个人见面\N{\r原文字幕}She thinks Amador is meeting with a man here in Los Angeles
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.68,0:03:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的名字叫马库斯·阿尔弗斯\N{\r原文字幕}by the name of Marcus Alvers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.84,0:03:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亚当对他做了些调查\N{\r原文字幕}Adam's done a workup on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们掌握了些背景信息 但是没有信息能确切表明他今天就在洛杉矶\N{\r原文字幕}We have some background, but there's nothing that places him definitively in Los Angeles today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.56,0:03:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就这些?\N{\r原文字幕}That's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.09,0:03:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国际警察组织那边呢? 他们有什么线索?\N{\r原文字幕}What about Interpol? What do they have on Alvers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.14,0:03:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的数据追踪有点滞后\N{\r原文字幕}Our data tracking's a little behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我们还拿不到那份报告\N{\r原文字幕}so we weren't able to access that report.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.85,0:03:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么会滞后呢?\N{\r原文字幕}Why are we behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我受伤的时候我们没有更新与欧洲的联系记录\N{\r原文字幕}We didn't update the European contact logs while I was down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.60,0:04:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,米歇尔,\N{\r原文字幕}Michelle
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.70,0:04:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是名出色的探员\N{\r原文字幕}you were the ranking agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.55,0:04:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为欧洲不是重点\N{\r原文字幕}I didn't think Europe was a priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.26,0:04:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然是的\N{\r原文字幕}Obviously it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.27,0:04:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那时发生了很多事\N{\r原文字幕}There was a lot going on at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.49,0:04:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.31,0:04:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回到工作吧\N{\r原文字幕}Let's get back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.59,0:04:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今晚剩下的时间我们要处理一下之前的失误\N{\r原文字幕}And let's try to ease up on the mistakes for the rest of the night
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.08,0:04:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有上百万的生命掌握在我们手中啊\N{\r原文字幕}as there are millions of lives depending on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.31,0:04:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,米歇尔...\N{\r原文字幕}Michelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进来\N{\r原文字幕}Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.55,0:04:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我刚和反恐局的人谈了下\N{\r原文字幕}I just got off with CTU.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.16,0:04:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有关病毒的情况怎么样?\N{\r原文字幕}What's the status on the virus?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.84,0:04:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 不是很好\N{\r原文字幕}Well, it's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,目前有限的情报证实了原来的猜测\N{\r原文字幕}The limited intelligence they have supports their original suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,病毒正在朝洛杉矶来\N{\r原文字幕}It's on its way to Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大卫 可能已经在洛杉矶了\N{\r原文字幕}David, it may already be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.50,0:04:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我们要做好准备以防他们将目标锁定其他城市\N{\r原文字幕}Then we should be prepared in case they target other cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:04:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在保护区的市民已经收到警报了\N{\r原文字幕}Our people in the security envelope have been alerted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.20,0:05:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信我 一切尽在掌握\N{\r原文字幕}Trust me, it's being handled.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.26,0:05:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你现在为什么不去休息一下呢?\N{\r原文字幕}Now, why don't you try and go get some rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.83,0:05:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有我盯着\N{\r原文字幕}I'm on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.55,0:05:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总统先生\N{\r原文字幕}Mr. President,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕默尔夫人想见您\N{\r原文字幕}Mrs. Palmer's here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.09,0:05:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请让她进来\N{\r原文字幕}Send her in, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.12,0:05:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提醒他们注意\N{\r原文字幕}Start waking people up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.78,0:05:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通知必要的内阁成员开会:\N{\r原文字幕}Set up a conference call with the appropriate cabinet members:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.27,0:05:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国土安全局 联邦调查局\N{\r原文字幕}Homeland Security, FBI,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国家卫生服务中心\N{\r原文字幕}National Health Services.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.49,0:05:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要所有人都行动起来\N{\r原文字幕}We're going to need everyone on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.96,0:05:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 总统先生\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.33,0:05:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,韦恩?\N{\r原文字幕}Wayne?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.24,0:05:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪莉, 我叫你来是帮忙\N{\r原文字幕}Sherry, I asked you here to help me,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.87,0:05:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是让事情变得更糟\N{\r原文字幕}not make things worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.32,0:05:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想让你去艾伦·米利肯家\N{\r原文字幕}I did not want you going to Alan Milliken's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.77,0:05:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好 放心 大卫 我没去\N{\r原文字幕}Well, relax, David. I didn't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.63,0:05:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你没去?  -没有\N{\r原文字幕}-You didn't go?  -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.53,0:05:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在通电话的时候\N{\r原文字幕}When we spoke on the phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.63,0:05:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说必须得要亲自和朱莉娅谈谈\N{\r原文字幕}you told me it was crucial that you speak to Julia in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 不过我改变主意了 我 我和她通过电话了\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, and I changed my mind. I-I spoke to her over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.53,0:05:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谈了什么?\N{\r原文字幕}About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.26,0:06:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,关于凯利失踪的事情\N{\r原文字幕}About Kelly's disappearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我问她是否可以查一下艾伦的手机\N{\r原文字幕}I asked her if she would check Alan's cell phone and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.52,0:06:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看有没有最近的通话记录\N{\r原文字幕}see if there were any recently made calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢?\N{\r原文字幕}And?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.77,0:06:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她不愿意\N{\r原文字幕}She wouldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.65,0:06:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不会接受一个拒绝的答复的 雪莉\N{\r原文字幕}You don't take no for an answer, Sherry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.58,0:06:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还有什么瞒着我?\N{\r原文字幕}What aren't you telling me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有 大卫 我发誓\N{\r原文字幕}Nothing, David, I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.79,0:06:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们打完电话后你如果不是去了米利肯家那你去哪儿了?\N{\r原文字幕}What have you been up to since we last talked if you weren't at Milliken's?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.23,0:06:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打电话\N{\r原文字幕}Making calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.00,0:06:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以在这里打啊\N{\r原文字幕}You could have made them from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.29,0:06:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 但我没有\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, but I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.12,0:06:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把车停在路边\N{\r原文字幕}I parked on the side of the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.63,0:06:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我开始打电话因为我等不及了\N{\r原文字幕}I started making calls because I didn't want to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉过你我们还有一线希望\N{\r原文字幕}I told you we have a small window of opportunity here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想先揭穿真相\N{\r原文字幕}I wanted to exploit the fact that Milliken may not have had time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.10,0:06:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,趁着米利肯还来不及掩盖他抓了凯利这件事\N{\r原文字幕}to cover his tracks when he had someone grab Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.32,0:06:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还有其他事要忙\N{\r原文字幕}I have other things to attend to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:06:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.19,0:07:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有其他事吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Is there anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.76,0:07:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\r原文字幕}That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.01,0:07:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好啊 尼娜\N{\r原文字幕}Hello, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带她去819号审讯室\N{\r原文字幕}Take her to interrogation 819.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.62,0:07:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是 长官\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.13,0:07:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安全措施怎么样?\N{\r原文字幕}What's the security configuration?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.53,0:07:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别担心 杰克 我们能搞定尼娜\N{\r原文字幕}Don't worry about it, Jack. We're handling Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.11,0:07:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞恩 你知道她的能耐\N{\r原文字幕}Ryan, you know what she's capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.04,0:07:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不是你现在要担心的问题\N{\r原文字幕}That's none of your concern right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.97,0:07:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要送你去做医疗检查\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sending you to medical to get checked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.82,0:07:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没事\N{\r原文字幕}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.07,0:07:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不这样认为\N{\r原文字幕}I don't think you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.32,0:07:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么回事?\N{\r原文字幕}What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:07:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们找到你注射海洛因的证据\N{\r原文字幕}We found evidence you've been injecting heroin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.43,0:08:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我我该滚开 杰克\N{\r原文字幕}Tell me I'm off here, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.49,0:08:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我是我弄错了\N{\r原文字幕}Tell me I'm wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.48,0:08:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕没有吧\N{\r原文字幕}I didn't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.01,0:08:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞恩 我没有走错一步\N{\r原文字幕}Ryan, I haven't missed a step.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.72,0:08:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很好\N{\r原文字幕}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.06,0:08:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也得替我自己考虑\N{\r原文字幕}I have to cover my ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.80,0:08:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我要带你去做检查  -你在浪费时间\N{\r原文字幕}-I need to get you checked out.  -You're wasting time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.86,0:08:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-金  -嗯?\N{\r原文字幕}-Kim.  -Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.22,0:08:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想你应该想知道你爸爸回来了\N{\r原文字幕}I thought you'd want to know your dad's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.77,0:08:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蔡斯呢?\N{\r原文字幕}What about Chase?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.96,0:08:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他几分钟后到\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, he's a few minutes behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.36,0:08:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.27,0:09:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金\N{\r原文字幕}Kim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.58,0:09:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸爸\N{\r原文字幕}Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.88,0:09:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 上帝 嗨!\N{\r原文字幕}Oh, God. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.21,0:09:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她被抓来了\N{\r原文字幕}She's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.64,0:09:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道 宝贝 我知道 来\N{\r原文字幕}I know, sweetheart. I know. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.98,0:09:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听我说 我要去向查佩尔汇报情况\N{\r原文字幕}Look, I have to debrief Chappelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.93,0:09:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,待会见 好吗?\N{\r原文字幕}I'll see you in a minute, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.34,0:09:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸爸 我知道你染上毒瘾了\N{\r原文字幕}Dad, I know about your drug problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.47,0:09:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么不告诉我?\N{\r原文字幕}Why didn't you come to me with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.43,0:10:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来\N{\r原文字幕}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.60,0:10:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来这儿\N{\r原文字幕}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.75,0:10:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很抱歉 宝贝\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.20,0:10:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.36,0:10:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我处境很尴尬\N{\r原文字幕}I was embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.68,0:10:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且这不是你的问题 现在也不是\N{\r原文字幕}And it wasn't your problem, and it still isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.87,0:10:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想让你担心\N{\r原文字幕}I didn't want you to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.42,0:10:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,戒掉了吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Well, is it over?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.64,0:10:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还没有\N{\r原文字幕}No, not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.80,0:10:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想我需要一个戒毒疗程 寻求帮助\N{\r原文字幕}I think I'm going to have to go into a program, and get some help.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.14,0:10:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-真的很抱歉  -没关系\N{\r原文字幕}-I'm so sorry.  -It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.65,0:10:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,查佩尔让我去医疗室做检查\N{\r原文字幕}Chappelle wants me to go into the clinic and get checked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.53,0:10:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们待会再谈这个 好吗?  -好的\N{\r原文字幕}-We'll talk about this later, okay?  -Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.49,0:10:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别担心\N{\r原文字幕}Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我爱你  -我也爱你\N{\r原文字幕}-I love you.  -Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.56,0:10:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.52,0:11:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰克\N{\r原文字幕}Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.60,0:11:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴看到你回来\N{\r原文字幕}I'm glad you're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.24,0:11:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有你在我们很不顺利\N{\r原文字幕}It's been difficult without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.90,0:11:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 克萝伊\N{\r原文字幕}Thanks, Chloe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.60,0:11:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-蔡斯  -嗯\N{\r原文字幕}-Chase.  -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.03,0:11:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我想和你谈一谈  -好吧\N{\r原文字幕}-Need to talk to you.  -Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.80,0:11:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去我办公室谈怎么样\N{\r原文字幕}Why don't you take a few minutes and come to my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 当然可以\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.87,0:11:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,米利肯先生?\N{\r原文字幕}Mr. Milliken?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.61,0:11:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,米利肯先生? 噢 天哪\N{\r原文字幕}Mr. Milliken? Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.87,0:11:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,米利肯夫人!\N{\r原文字幕}Mrs. Milliken!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.52,0:12:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快来!\N{\r原文字幕}Come quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.67,0:12:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快!\N{\r原文字幕}Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.21,0:12:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿\N{\r原文字幕}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.57,0:12:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的手怎么样了?\N{\r原文字幕}How's the hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.62,0:12:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事\N{\r原文字幕}It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.44,0:12:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,查佩尔是怎么知道的?\N{\r原文字幕}How'd Chappelle find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.69,0:12:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道 这不重要了\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know, it doesn't really matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.25,0:12:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,外面发生什么事了?\N{\r原文字幕}What's going on out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.70,0:12:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔梅达要审问尼娜\N{\r原文字幕}Almeida's going to be interrogating Nina,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会通过连线看的\N{\r原文字幕}and I'll follow it from a feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.60,0:12:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好 很好\N{\r原文字幕}Okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.59,0:12:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让托尼加强守卫戒备\N{\r原文字幕}Make sure Tony puts double security on the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.01,0:12:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一有消息马上告诉我\N{\r原文字幕}Get back to me as soon as she gives you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.43,0:12:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲍尔探员 按住这里\N{\r原文字幕}Agent Bauer, keep pressure here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.03,0:12:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Sure. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.19,0:12:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰克\N{\r原文字幕}Jack,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.36,0:12:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就要知道关于我的一些事了 你不会高兴的起来\N{\r原文字幕}you're about to find something out about me that's not going to make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.83,0:12:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在说什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.95,0:12:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好意思 你介意出去一下吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Excuse me. Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.34,0:12:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有个女儿\N{\r原文字幕}I've got a daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.95,0:13:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-女儿?  -我一个月前突然知道的\N{\r原文字幕}-A daughter?  -It was sprung on me a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.11,0:13:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的妈妈把她送到我那里 然后离开了\N{\r原文字幕}Her mother dropped her off, and she split.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.36,0:13:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说来话长\N{\r原文字幕}It's a long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.15,0:13:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金知道这件事情吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Does Kim know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.86,0:13:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.11,0:13:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你告诉她的?\N{\r原文字幕}From you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.87,0:13:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还没有机会亲自和她谈谈\N{\r原文字幕}I haven't had a chance to talk to her myself yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.97,0:13:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要和她说清楚 蔡斯 你明白我的意思吗?\N{\r原文字幕}You square this with her, Chase, you understand me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.02,0:13:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妥善处理\N{\r原文字幕}Just make that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦尼娜说了什么就马上告诉我\N{\r原文字幕}And get back to me as soon as Nina gives you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.88,0:13:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会的\N{\r原文字幕}I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.50,0:13:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Are we up yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.49,0:13:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了 视频已经接入\N{\r原文字幕}Yep. Video's piped in,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.36,0:13:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,声音分析 器官监视 图像转录\N{\r原文字幕}voice analysis, vitals, transcription.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.19,0:13:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-全都准备好了  -Nick 收到么?\N{\r原文字幕}-We're all set. -Nick, do you copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是的 能听见  -准备开始了\N{\r原文字幕}-Yeah, I read you.  -We're ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.87,0:13:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 现在开始录制到硬盘\N{\r原文字幕}All right, recording to hard drive now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.61,0:13:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那 托尼来审问吗?\N{\r原文字幕}So, Tony's doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.97,0:14:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.75,0:14:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不会觉得奇怪?\N{\r原文字幕}Is that going to be weird for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.20,0:14:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么意思?\N{\r原文字幕}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.02,0:14:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和尼娜不是 不是交往过吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Didn't-didn't he and Nina go out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.75,0:14:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.05,0:14:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了吗?\N{\r原文字幕}We set?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.75,0:14:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.40,0:14:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\r原文字幕}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.59,0:14:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把眼睛部位提到高分辨率\N{\r原文字幕}I want you to do a hi-res on her eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.49,0:14:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她累了\N{\r原文字幕}She's tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.92,0:14:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许我们可以捕获些信息\N{\r原文字幕}We might be able to pick up a tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.62,0:14:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们之间没什么吧?\N{\r原文字幕}So, we all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.95,0:14:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 没什么\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah. We're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.67,0:14:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\r原文字幕}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.23,0:14:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开始吧\N{\r原文字幕}Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.47,0:14:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2号监视器提到高分辨率\N{\r原文字幕}I got the hi-res on monitor two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.04,0:14:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,托尼\N{\r原文字幕}Tony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.65,0:15:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没想到今天会看到你\N{\r原文字幕}Didn't know I was gonna see you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我们想要什么\N{\r原文字幕}You know what we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.22,0:15:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要在迈克尔 阿马多尔释放病毒前找到他\N{\r原文字幕}We need to find Michael Amador before he unloads the virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.63,0:15:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经把我所知道的都告诉杰克了\N{\r原文字幕}I've already told Jack everything I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.10,0:15:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要你告诉我\N{\r原文字幕}Well, I want you to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.26,0:15:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,首先是杰克 现在又是你\N{\r原文字幕}First Jack, now you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.61,0:15:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯... 这让我想起了什么呢?\N{\r原文字幕}Hmm... what does that remind me of?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你告诉杰克 阿马多尔会去联系一个叫马库斯·阿尔弗斯的人\N{\r原文字幕}You told Jack that Amador might try to contact a Marcus Alvers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.73,0:15:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那 我们在哪能找到阿尔弗斯?\N{\r原文字幕}So, where do we look for Alvers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.09,0:15:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不错的戒指啊\N{\r原文字幕}That's a nice ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.64,0:15:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个幸运的女孩是谁?\N{\r原文字幕}Who's the lucky girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.66,0:15:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过希望你能做好背景调查 因为\N{\r原文字幕}Hope you did a background check, though, 'cause
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.05,0:15:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也不希望犯两次同样的错误吧\N{\r原文字幕}you don't want to make the same mistake twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.98,0:15:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会回到监狱去\N{\r原文字幕}You're going back to prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.10,0:15:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你很有可能会背上叛国罪\N{\r原文字幕}There's a good chance you'll be executed as a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.43,0:15:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道你如果和我们合作的话 你有可能救自己一命\N{\r原文字幕}Now you know if you cooperate, you may be able to save your own life,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.38,0:15:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你却在拖延时间\N{\r原文字幕}but you're stalling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.73,0:16:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这说明你知道什么\N{\r原文字幕}Which means you know something
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.09,0:16:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还以为你可以耍花招\N{\r原文字幕}and you still think there's a play you can make,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.37,0:16:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只不过现在不是时候\N{\r原文字幕}only now's not the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.68,0:16:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说话很尖锐\N{\r原文字幕}Very incisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.54,0:16:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但愿你的妻子喜欢你这点\N{\r原文字幕}I hope your wife appreciates that about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.36,0:16:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不跟我说说阿尔弗斯呢?\N{\r原文字幕}Why don't you tell me about Alvers?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.37,0:16:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只知道他只和阿马多尔做生意\N{\r原文字幕}All I know is that he works only with Amador.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.97,0:16:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我并不认识他\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know him personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.01,0:16:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只能找到一些零散的医疗记录\N{\r原文字幕}All we've been able to dig up on him are a few random medical records
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用的是他的化名\N{\r原文字幕}under one of his known aliases.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他做过膝盖磁共振\N{\r原文字幕}He had an MRI on one of his knees,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.08,0:16:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里有个抗生素的药方\N{\r原文字幕}there's a prescription for antibiotics,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.34,0:16:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用来治艾滋病的...\N{\r原文字幕}treated for HIV...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.20,0:16:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的脉搏加快\N{\r原文字幕}Her pulse is spiking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.39,0:16:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人和马库斯·阿尔弗斯发生关系没用保护措施哦\N{\r原文字幕}Someone hasn't been using protection with Marcus Alvers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.60,0:16:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她可能和他发生过关系\N{\r原文字幕}She's probably had sex with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.05,0:16:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听着 尼娜\N{\r原文字幕}See, Nina,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.52,0:17:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我隔壁房间的同事告诉我\N{\r原文字幕}my colleagues in the next room tell me that something in those
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.11,0:17:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些医疗记录上有些东西使你担忧\N{\r原文字幕}medical records concerns you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.61,0:17:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我猜不是因为膝盖吧\N{\r原文字幕}I'm guessing it's not the knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.88,0:17:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来找阿尔弗斯\N{\r原文字幕}I'm here to see Alvers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.42,0:17:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马库斯.\N{\r原文字幕}Marcus
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.29,0:17:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迈克尔.\N{\r原文字幕}Michael
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.82,0:17:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,旅途怎样?\N{\r原文字幕}How was your trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.75,0:17:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很有意思\N{\r原文字幕}Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.74,0:17:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还是不明白你为什么要去墨西哥冒那么大的风险\N{\r原文字幕}I still don't understand why you risked so much down in Mexico,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.99,0:17:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不直接来这\N{\r原文字幕}why you didn't come here directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.00,0:17:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2.4亿美元让我值得冒这个险\N{\r原文字幕}240 million dollars made it worth the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.60,0:18:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼娜怎么样?\N{\r原文字幕}What about Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.91,0:18:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果她没有被炸弹炸死的话\N{\r原文字幕}If she wasn't killed by the bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.75,0:18:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我肯定买主在发现她没有运送病毒之后会好好款待她\N{\r原文字幕}I'm sure our buyers took care of her once they found out she didn't deliver the virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.95,0:18:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎样 她都无关紧要了\N{\r原文字幕}Either way, she's out of the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.65,0:18:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但愿如此\N{\r原文字幕}I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.10,0:18:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她可以揭发我们\N{\r原文字幕}She can point to both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.34,0:18:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在任何人发现我们之前我们已经远走高飞了\N{\r原文字幕}We'll be long gone before anyone starts looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金.\N{\r原文字幕}Kim
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.95,0:18:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听我说 我知道自从我回来后我们还没有说过话\N{\r原文字幕}Look, I know we haven't talked since I got back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.53,0:18:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 没有\N{\r原文字幕}No, we haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.53,0:18:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你在想什么\N{\r原文字幕}I know what you must be thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:18:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你要给我个机会解释啊\N{\r原文字幕}but you need to give me a chance to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.96,0:19:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道该怎么想\N{\r原文字幕}I don't know what to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.27,0:19:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听我说 我很高兴你没事\N{\r原文字幕}Look, I'm happy that you're okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.36,0:19:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是这件事...\N{\r原文字幕}but this thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.35,0:19:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有个孩子 蔡斯\N{\r原文字幕}you have a baby, Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.38,0:19:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在一起已经三个多月了\N{\r原文字幕}We've been together for more than three months,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.98,0:19:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你竟然还一直瞒着我\N{\r原文字幕}and you kept this secret from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.07,0:19:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孩子的母亲是谁? 她什么时候插进来的?\N{\r原文字幕}Who's the mother? Where does she fit into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.28,0:19:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这正是我想跟你说的\N{\r原文字幕}That's what I want to talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.25,0:19:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也是一个月前才知道我有个女儿的\N{\r原文字幕}I didn't know I had a daughter until a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.29,0:19:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么会不知道?\N{\r原文字幕}How could you not know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.44,0:19:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安吉拉的妈妈和我去年交往了\N{\r原文字幕}Angela's mother and I went out last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.72,0:19:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经分手了 分手的时候\N{\r原文字幕}Okay, it's over. And when it ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她从来没告诉我她怀孕了\N{\r原文字幕}she never told me she was pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.39,0:19:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个月前她打电话告诉我她有个孩子\N{\r原文字幕}Now she calls a month ago and tells me she has a baby,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.96,0:19:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是孩子的父亲\N{\r原文字幕}and that I'm the father.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.76,0:19:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她现在有麻烦 不能照顾孩子\N{\r原文字幕}And she's in trouble, and she can't handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.18,0:19:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我害怕别人会发现\N{\r原文字幕}I was afraid to let people find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.34,0:19:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我害怕这会影响我们的关系\N{\r原文字幕}I was afraid it was gonna mess us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.16,0:19:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你告诉克萝伊了\N{\r原文字幕}But you told Chloe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.02,0:19:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,克萝伊和我姐姐在帮我照顾孩子\N{\r原文字幕}Chloe and my sister have been helping me take care of the baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.68,0:19:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她是我的好朋友\N{\r原文字幕}She's a good friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.35,0:19:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 蔡斯?\N{\r原文字幕}Excuse me. Chase?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.92,0:19:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果安吉拉醒了 你让我告诉你的吧\N{\r原文字幕}You wanted me to let you know when Angela woke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.14,0:19:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谢谢  -不用谢\N{\r原文字幕}-Thank you.  -Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.20,0:20:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金 我也和你一样困惑\N{\r原文字幕}Kim, I'm just as confused as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.04,0:20:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我只知道我爱你\N{\r原文字幕}But all I know is that I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.00,0:20:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也开始喜欢上安吉拉\N{\r原文字幕}And I'm falling in love with Angela, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须处理好这个事情\N{\r原文字幕}And I need to make this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.77,0:20:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去吧\N{\r原文字幕}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.36,0:20:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼娜审问得怎么样?\N{\r原文字幕}What's happening with Nina in interrogation?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.15,0:20:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们有所发现\N{\r原文字幕}They're getting something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.42,0:20:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.25,0:20:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔弗斯和尼娜的关系可能比我们想象的更密切\N{\r原文字幕}The connection between Alvers and Nina might be deeper than we thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.28,0:20:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你最好希望她不是在耍你\N{\r原文字幕}You'd better hope she's not just spinning your wheels,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.07,0:20:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为她知道怎么和我们周旋\N{\r原文字幕}because she knows how to manipulate our interrogation protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.57,0:21:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,托尼知道该怎么做\N{\r原文字幕}Tony knows what he's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.14,0:21:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 我要去见克萝伊\N{\r原文字幕}Okay, fine. Look, I need to get together with Chloe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.07,0:21:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要所有有关阿马多尔的调查内容\N{\r原文字幕}I need everything that she's got on the Amador investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.18,0:21:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先别急\N{\r原文字幕}Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.13,0:21:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞恩 你在浪费我的时间\N{\r原文字幕}Ryan, look, you're wasting my time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.10,0:21:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我迁就你去做了体检\N{\r原文字幕}Now, I humored you with the physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.06,0:21:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都知道我的血样检测\N{\r原文字幕}And we both know that my blood work's gonna come back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.19,0:21:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会查出有毒品 这已经够了\N{\r原文字幕}with trace amounts of opiates, but enough is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.32,0:21:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,检查总部的瑞伊·普拉切基来了\N{\r原文字幕}Rae Plachecki from the inspector general's office is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.94,0:21:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她想和你谈谈\N{\r原文字幕}She wants to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-现在不是时候  -就是现在\N{\r原文字幕}-Well, this is not the time.  -Actually, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.56,0:21:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要和她谈谈\N{\r原文字幕}You'll talk to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.65,0:21:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们再决定你是否可以继续工作\N{\r原文字幕}then we'll evaluate whether you can go back to work or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.59,0:21:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\N{\r原文字幕}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.47,0:21:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞伊·普拉切基 这是杰克·鲍尔\N{\r原文字幕}Rae Plachecki, this is Jack Bauer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.22,0:21:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我们的规矩 杰克 我要问你一些问题\N{\r原文字幕}You know the drill, Jack. I'm gonna ask you some questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.75,0:21:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我想让你知道 我是站在你这边的\N{\r原文字幕}but I want you to know, I'm on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.98,0:21:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只是想证实注射海洛因是你掩饰身份的需要\N{\r原文字幕}We just want to establish that this heroin addiction was a necessary part of your cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.41,0:21:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我掩饰身份的需要\N{\r原文字幕}It was necessary to maintain my cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.90,0:21:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以了吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Are we done now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.67,0:21:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐下 杰克\N{\r原文字幕}Sit down, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.32,0:22:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是瑞伊·普拉切基\N{\r原文字幕}This is Rae Plachecki.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.50,0:22:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在时间是凌晨2:31\N{\r原文字幕}The time is 2:31 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.67,0:22:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是对杰克·鲍尔 反恐局侦查部部长的审讯\N{\r原文字幕}This is the interrogation of Jack Bauer, director of field ops, CTU.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.46,0:22:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞恩·查佩尔在场\N{\r原文字幕}Ryan Chappelle is present.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.95,0:22:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杰克,\N{\r原文字幕}Jack
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.07,0:22:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我们你怎样在拉姆·萨拉扎身边掩饰你的身份的\N{\r原文字幕}tell us how you established your cover with Ramon Salazar.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.52,0:22:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是先和萨拉扎兄弟两人接触\N{\r原文字幕}I first came in contact with the Salazars
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.53,0:22:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大约两年前\N{\r原文字幕}approximately two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.58,0:22:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们是墨西哥新兴的贩毒集团\N{\r原文字幕}They were an up-and-coming narcotic cartel, coming out of Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.95,0:22:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你什么时候见到阿马多尔的?\N{\r原文字幕}So, when did you meet Amador?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.45,0:22:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在反恐局工作时认识他吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Did you know him when you were working at CTU?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.67,0:22:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说吧 尼娜\N{\r原文字幕}Tell me something, Nina,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.06,0:22:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道你这是在做什么交易吗?\N{\r原文字幕}what kind of a deal you think you're gonna cut?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.13,0:22:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你背叛了所有你认识的人\N{\r原文字幕}You've betrayed everybody you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.22,0:22:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,包括我\N{\r原文字幕}including me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.48,0:22:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你杀了杰克的妻子\N{\r原文字幕}You murdered Jack's wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.20,0:23:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你帮助恐怖分子把核弹偷运到这个国家\N{\r原文字幕}You helped terrorists smuggle a nuclear bomb into this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.88,0:23:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要帮他们把致命的病毒投入人群中\N{\r原文字幕}You're helping to unleash a deadly virus into the general population.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.70,0:23:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不懂\N{\r原文字幕}Help me understand this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.65,0:23:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想要干什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.77,0:23:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做一个谋杀犯对你有什么好处?\N{\r原文字幕}What is it you get out of being a mass murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.14,0:23:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的脖子在流血\N{\r原文字幕}Your neck is bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.50,0:24:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,道尔顿 发现什么没有?\N{\r原文字幕}Dalton, what do you got?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.78,0:24:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,目前 她的反应都是下意识的\N{\r原文字幕}So far, the only reactions we're getting from her are subliminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.56,0:24:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果她再不招供 我们就得在她的器官反应上再下功夫\N{\r原文字幕}If she's not gonna say anything, we need to be more plugged in to her vitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.58,0:24:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以带她去7号审讯室 给她做个被动反应测试\N{\r原文字幕}We can take her down to seven, give her a passive response test.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.38,0:24:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,7号审讯室不够安全\N{\r原文字幕}Seven's not secure enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.43,0:24:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就让她待在这\N{\r原文字幕}She stays here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.55,0:24:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理查兹在哪?\N{\r原文字幕}Where's Richards?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.99,0:24:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他正候着\N{\r原文字幕}He's waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.69,0:24:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 让他进来\N{\r原文字幕}All right, let's bring him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.11,0:24:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让达伦进来\N{\r原文字幕}Send Darren in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.33,0:24:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尼娜 我想你没见过达伦·理查兹吧\N{\r原文字幕}Nina, I don't think you've met Darren Richards.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.96,0:24:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是在你离开后加入我们的\N{\r原文字幕}He joined us after you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.27,0:25:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 达伦\N{\r原文字幕}Hello, Darren.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.42,0:25:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别介意\N{\r原文字幕}Don't take it personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.83,0:25:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不怎么喜欢说话\N{\r原文字幕}He doesn't talk much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.98,0:25:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 有些事情我不明白 杰克\N{\r原文字幕}Uh, something's not connecting up for me, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.09,0:25:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说你直到二月初才进入萨拉扎集团\N{\r原文字幕}You say that you weren't in with the Salazars until early February,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.19,0:25:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是你是在12月底开始注射海洛因的\N{\r原文字幕}but the first time you started using was late December.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.55,0:25:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这六周期间你吸毒没有理由啊\N{\r原文字幕}That's six weeks of shooting up for the benefit of no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.90,0:25:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我遗漏了什么吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Am I missing something?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.21,0:25:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想装得更像一个无赖\N{\r原文字幕}I was trying to pass myself off as a junkie.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.94,0:25:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想充分做好准备\N{\r原文字幕}I wanted to be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.55,0:25:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么意思 做准备?\N{\r原文字幕}What do you mean, "prepared"?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.90,0:25:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,萨拉扎兄弟一生都在和毒品打交道\N{\r原文字幕}The Salazars lived their entire lives in the drug world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.63,0:25:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我不吸毒\N{\r原文字幕}If I couldn't handle the narcotics that went with that territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.53,0:25:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会发现我是警察 他们会杀了我\N{\r原文字幕}they'd have known I was a cop, and they'd have killed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.83,0:26:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要处理好这个\N{\r原文字幕}I needed to be able to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.85,0:26:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 这说的过去 但是直到一月份\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, that makes sense, but in January,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.17,0:26:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你注射海洛因的时候\N{\r原文字幕}when you were putting needles in your arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.48,0:26:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也没有记录显示你和这些人见过面...\N{\r原文字幕}you didn't have a meeting on the books with these guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.19,0:26:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许会要一年 这你们都知道\N{\r原文字幕}it could have been a year, for all you knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.85,0:26:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在说什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.16,0:26:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在努力证实你吸毒\N{\r原文字幕}I am trying to establish incontrovertible evidence that you did drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.02,0:26:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是为了掩饰身份... 如果我把你刚才讲的提交上去\N{\r原文字幕}as part of your cover... if I submit what you just told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.31,0:26:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是不足以证明你的清白的 杰克\N{\r原文字幕}it's not gonna hold up, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.06,0:26:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想让我说什么?!\N{\r原文字幕}What do you want me to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.96,0:26:22.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我为了混到这些人当中去我吸了毒\N{\r原文字幕}I did drugs to get in with these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.99,0:26:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我混进去了!\N{\r原文字幕}and I got in with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.20,0:26:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管有多难 我已经没有吸毒了\N{\r原文字幕}And no matter how difficult it's been, I don't use anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.96,0:26:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听着\N{\r原文字幕}Look,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.96,0:26:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就这样写 也许会过关\N{\r原文字幕}I'll write it up that way, and maybe it'll fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.10,0:26:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我觉得你可能会有麻烦\N{\r原文字幕}but I just think you're gonna have a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.23,0:26:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你从来没有告诉过任何人 即使是你的搭档\N{\r原文字幕}because you never told anyone, not even your partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.65,0:26:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这有点可疑\N{\r原文字幕}That's suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.93,0:26:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞伊 你知道我的过去\N{\r原文字幕}Rae, you know my history.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.38,0:26:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自从我妻子去世后我一直很痛苦\N{\r原文字幕}I've had a very difficult time since my wife passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.15,0:26:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我告诉别人我要为了查案子去吸毒\N{\r原文字幕}If I'd told anyone that I was using drugs to develop a case,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.93,0:27:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会误解的\N{\r原文字幕}they would have misinterpreted,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.21,0:27:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能冒那个险\N{\r原文字幕}and I couldn't afford that risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.49,0:27:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 就看他们怎么想了\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah, well, that's what they're gonna do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.83,0:27:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞伊,\N{\r原文字幕}Rae,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.89,0:27:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们就当杰克从一月底开始吸毒\N{\r原文字幕}let's put down that Jack started using heroin in late January,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.86,0:27:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在和萨拉扎第一次见面之后\N{\r原文字幕}after the first meeting with Salazar was established.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.79,0:27:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你的帮忙 瑞恩\N{\r原文字幕}I appreciate what you're trying to do, Ryan,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.82,0:27:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是事实不是这样\N{\r原文字幕}but that's not what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.98,0:27:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是想让我们少打几份报告\N{\r原文字幕}Just trying to save us all some paperwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.63,0:27:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没意见\N{\r原文字幕}I'm okay with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.24,0:27:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有\N{\r原文字幕}I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.75,0:27:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是从12月开始吸毒的\N{\r原文字幕}I started using in December.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.25,0:27:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有什么好隐瞒的\N{\r原文字幕}I've got nothing to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.94,0:27:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里需要的是结果\N{\r原文字幕}This office demands results,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.25,0:27:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我能提供的:\N{\r原文字幕}and that's what I provide:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.57,0:27:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结果\N{\r原文字幕}results.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.80,0:27:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.09,0:27:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以回去工作了吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Can I get back to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.08,0:27:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还不行 杰克\N{\r原文字幕}Not quite yet, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.54,0:27:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 很安全 我们已经拿到了\N{\r原文字幕}No, it's secure and we have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.70,0:27:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切按计划行事\N{\r原文字幕}It will be as arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.75,0:28:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他一小时后到\N{\r原文字幕}He'll be here in an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.18,0:28:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要在他们释放病毒之前我们有足够的时间离开这个国家就行\N{\r原文字幕}Just as long as we have enough time to leave the country before they let this virus out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.11,0:28:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请坐\N{\r原文字幕}Please be seated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.04,0:28:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,五个小时前\N{\r原文字幕}Five hours ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.30,0:28:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我向公众发表了关于全国恐怖威胁的声明\N{\r原文字幕}I went public with a statement that there was a domestic terror threat,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.63,0:28:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们以为已经过去了\N{\r原文字幕}but it had passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.88,0:28:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是现在看来还为时过早\N{\r原文字幕}And now it appears that that was premature.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.12,0:28:30.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女士们先生们\N{\r原文字幕}Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.03,0:28:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在是否面临病毒释放的威胁?\N{\r原文字幕}do we or do we not have a threat of this virus being released?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.42,0:28:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总统先生\N{\r原文字幕}Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.44,0:28:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕我们还不能确切地回答这个问题\N{\r原文字幕}I'm afraid we can't answer that question with any kind of certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.01,0:28:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么说 哈蒙德先生?\N{\r原文字幕}What can you tell me, Mr. Hammond?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.82,0:28:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,线索表明迈克尔 阿马多尔\N{\r原文字幕}What few leads we have indicate that Michael Amador has
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.45,0:28:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,手握病毒并且已经在洛杉矶\N{\r原文字幕}the virus and is in Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.01,0:28:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出于什么目的 我们不知道\N{\r原文字幕}For what purpose, we can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.16,0:28:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我们要在洛杉矶做好防范的准备\N{\r原文字幕}Then we have to prepare for defensive action here in Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.16,0:28:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鉴于此 在各大城市\N{\r原文字幕}And for that matter, in all of our major cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.76,0:28:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总统先生\N{\r原文字幕}Mr. President,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.91,0:28:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我们国土安全局的立场\N{\r原文字幕}you know our position here at Homeland Security.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.42,0:29:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们觉得对公众坦白\N{\r原文字幕}We think being forthright with the public and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.92,0:29:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他们做好准备是正确的选择\N{\r原文字幕}making such preparations in the open is the correct course.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.24,0:29:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有 我们要估测一下这个方案的不足\N{\r原文字幕}Again, we have to assess the downside of that course.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.20,0:29:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没意见 总统先生\N{\r原文字幕}I have no problem with that, Mr. President,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.24,0:29:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是我们要意识到我们正在跟时间赛跑\N{\r原文字幕}as long as we realize we are working against a clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.99,0:29:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望所有在座的部门制定出内公开的秘密\N{\r原文字幕}I want all departments present to work up an open versus covert
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.61,0:29:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,牵制策略 30分钟后交给我\N{\r原文字幕}containment strategy and report back to me in 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.98,0:29:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同时 我希望卫生服务发布指导方针\N{\r原文字幕}In the meantime, I want Health Services to issue guidelines,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.35,0:29:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是只在内部分发行\N{\r原文字幕}but only to be distributed internally.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.19,0:29:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就这样\N{\r原文字幕}That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.50,0:29:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会在办公室\N{\r原文字幕}I'll be in my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.42,0:29:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大卫.\N{\r原文字幕}David
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.26,0:29:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请让我们单独谈谈 亚伦\N{\r原文字幕}Give us a second, please, Aaron.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.34,0:29:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 先生\N{\r原文字幕}Of course, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.00,0:29:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,情报中心刚接到一个电话\N{\r原文字幕}Secret Service just received a phone call
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.26,0:29:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是从西洛杉矶警察分部打来的\N{\r原文字幕}from the west Los Angeles police department.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.13,0:30:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾伦·米利肯死了\N{\r原文字幕}Alan Milliken is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.00,0:30:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.60,0:30:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,15分钟前尸体在他家里被发现\N{\r原文字幕}He was found 15 minutes ago in his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.82,0:30:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有迹象表明死于心脏病\N{\r原文字幕}All signs point to a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.86,0:30:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不可能\N{\r原文字幕}It isn't possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.87,0:30:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但千真万确\N{\r原文字幕}Well, apparently, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.50,0:30:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说雪莉大约一个小时前在去那里的路上\N{\r原文字幕}You told me Sherry was on her way over there about an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.25,0:30:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她改变了主意\N{\r原文字幕}She changed her mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.51,0:30:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在车上打了电话\N{\r原文字幕}Made some phone calls from her car.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.61,0:30:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后直接回来这里\N{\r原文字幕}Came straight back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.88,0:30:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大卫 这是她跟你说的吗?\N{\r原文字幕}David, is that what she told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.21,0:30:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.99,0:30:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她现在在哪?\N{\r原文字幕}And where is she now?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.45,0:30:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在休息\N{\r原文字幕}Resting.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.22,0:30:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亚伦 带我去见雪莉\N{\r原文字幕}Aaron, take me to Sherry.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.81,0:30:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是 先生\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.49,0:30:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她在这边\N{\r原文字幕}She's right this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.74,0:30:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的轮班还没结束吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Hasn't your shift ended?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.85,0:30:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我留下来了\N{\r原文字幕}I stayed on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.04,0:30:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得今天有很多困难 我想留下来帮你\N{\r原文字幕}I sense it's a difficult day, and I wanted to be here for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.21,0:30:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谢谢你  -就在这里 先生\N{\r原文字幕}-I appreciate that.  -Right in there, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.41,0:31:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪莉.\N{\r原文字幕}Sherry
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.28,0:31:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大卫.\N{\r原文字幕}David
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.47,0:31:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么啦?\N{\r原文字幕}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.20,0:31:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾伦·米利肯死了\N{\r原文字幕}Alan Milliken is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.56,0:31:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么? 怎么死的?\N{\r原文字幕}What? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.45,0:31:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不如你来告诉我?\N{\r原文字幕}Why don't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.92,0:31:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你什么意思?\N{\r原文字幕}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.42,0:31:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟你说了 我没去那\N{\r原文字幕}I told you, I didn't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.78,0:31:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你告诉我了\N{\r原文字幕}I know what you told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.21,0:31:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你坐在车里面给她打了电话\N{\r原文字幕}You sat in your car, you made some phone calls,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.84,0:31:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后你直接过来了\N{\r原文字幕}and you came straight here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.18,0:31:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 事实就是这样\N{\r原文字幕}Yes, and that's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.51,0:31:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你不介意警方检查你的手机\N{\r原文字幕}Then you won't mind the police checking your cell phone
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.64,0:31:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及你今天晚上用过的车吧\N{\r原文字幕}and the car you used tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.25,0:31:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道...\N{\r原文字幕}You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.42,0:31:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要我\N{\r原文字幕}you asked me
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.41,0:31:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帮你解决这个问题 我照做了\N{\r原文字幕}to take care of a problem, and I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.81,0:31:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想让警方检查我的手机通话记录 那么\N{\r原文字幕}If you want the police to check phone logs, then
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.05,0:31:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你应该让他们先检查你的\N{\r原文字幕}have them check yours first.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.87,0:31:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,记住 你今天晚上打电话给我了\N{\r原文字幕}Because remember? You called me tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.94,0:31:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我因为你才来这里 大卫\N{\r原文字幕}I am here because of you, David.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.75,0:32:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到底发生了什么事 雪莉?\N{\r原文字幕}What happened, Sherry?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.96,0:32:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去那只是想和朱莉娅谈谈\N{\r原文字幕}I went over to the house just to speak to Julia.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.23,0:32:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾伦打断了我们\N{\r原文字幕}Alan interrupted us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.31,0:32:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们吵起来 然后...\N{\r原文字幕}There was an argument and...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.84,0:32:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他突然心脏病发作\N{\r原文字幕}he had a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.81,0:32:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警方会调查的\N{\r原文字幕}There's going to be an investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.00,0:32:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要说实话\N{\r原文字幕}You're going to have to tell the truth about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.19,0:32:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实救不了我们任何一个\N{\r原文字幕}The truth isn't going to save either one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.76,0:32:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们将听到的就是我是代表你去那儿的\N{\r原文字幕}All they're going to hear is that I was there on your behalf
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.73,0:32:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去阻止艾伦和你竞争总统选举\N{\r原文字幕}to prevent Alan from meddling with your presidency,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.96,0:32:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是正常死亡\N{\r原文字幕}and that he died from natural causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.77,0:33:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么你觉得纽约时报\N{\r原文字幕}Now, how do you think that's going to play out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.60,0:33:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会在接下来的六个月里怎样报道这件事情吗?\N{\r原文字幕}in the New York Times for the next six months?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.85,0:33:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对艾伦做了什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What did you do to Alan?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.34,0:33:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,实话说 大卫\N{\r原文字幕}Honestly, David,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.23,0:33:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么也没有\N{\r原文字幕}nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.50,0:33:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么也没做\N{\r原文字幕}Absolutely nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.89,0:33:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金,\N{\r原文字幕}Kim,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.74,0:33:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把监控数据接入到了你的系统\N{\r原文字幕}I transferred that feed to your system.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.36,0:33:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要我现在帮你转进来吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Do you want me to pull it up for you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.24,0:33:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\r原文字幕}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.98,0:33:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得她不会向他们招供的\N{\r原文字幕}I don't think she's going to give them anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.18,0:33:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们得自己找到马库斯·阿尔弗斯\N{\r原文字幕}We're going to have to find Marcus Alvers by ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.61,0:33:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能做什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.50,0:33:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 我和亚洲那边取得了联系\N{\r原文字幕}Um, I followed up on some of those Asian connections,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.09,0:33:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是同时 我还有些东西想让你看\N{\r原文字幕}but in the meantime, there's something I want you to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.39,0:33:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-内容很多  -这是什么?\N{\r原文字幕}-It's a long shot.  -What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.32,0:33:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马库斯·阿尔弗斯三年来待过的城市的名单\N{\r原文字幕}A list of cities where Marcus Alvers has been in the last three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.92,0:33:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个地方都只待了几天\N{\r原文字幕}Each time only for a couple of days.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.41,0:34:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许他是去见某个人\N{\r原文字幕}Maybe he was meeting somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.31,0:34:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把这个和我们资料库里有嫌疑的地方交叉查询\N{\r原文字幕}Cross it with the other suspects in our database.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.32,0:34:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发现了什么就告诉我 好吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Let me know what you come up with, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.63,0:34:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\r原文字幕}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.70,0:34:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听着 我不知道你们为什么要再审问一遍\N{\r原文字幕}Look, I don't know why we have to go through this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.64,0:34:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经回答了\N{\r原文字幕}I already answered that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.52,0:34:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了 埃德蒙兹?\N{\r原文字幕}What is it, Edmunds?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.77,0:34:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉你尼娜的最新情况\N{\r原文字幕}Just wanted to give you an update on Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.95,0:34:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瑞伊 可以暂停一下吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Rae, could you pause that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.82,0:34:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她有透露什么关于阿尔弗斯的消息吗?\N{\r原文字幕}She give us anything new on Alvers?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.47,0:34:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\r原文字幕}No,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.93,0:34:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了她可能认识他\N{\r原文字幕}other than the probability she knew him personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.67,0:34:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她不愿意合作\N{\r原文字幕}She's not cooperating.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.07,0:34:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的人在干什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What are we doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.44,0:34:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理查兹在给她用刑\N{\r原文字幕}Richards is working on her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.70,0:34:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得这是个错误\N{\r原文字幕}I think that's a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.66,0:34:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-为什么?  -我觉得不应该让和她没有共事过的人去审问她\N{\r原文字幕}-Why?  -I don't think anybody should be in there that hasn't worked with her before,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.69,0:34:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不知道她的能耐 会被利用的\N{\r原文字幕}doesn't know what she's capable of. She'll manipulate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.85,0:34:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,理查兹只是让她承受痛苦\N{\r原文字幕}All Richards does is inflict pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.20,0:34:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可能被她利用的\N{\r原文字幕}There's no way for her to manipulate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.73,0:34:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\r原文字幕}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.32,0:35:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还想忍受多少折磨 尼娜?\N{\r原文字幕}How much more of this you want to endure, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.72,0:35:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想就这样了\N{\r原文字幕}I think this is about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.43,0:35:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-她刺到动脉了!  -米歇尔 快叫医生!\N{\r原文字幕}-She hit an artery!  -Michelle, call medical!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.22,0:35:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 不 她留了太多血 我们得现在就把她送到医务室去!\N{\r原文字幕}No, she's bleeding too much. We got to take her there now!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.57,0:35:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-通知安全中心!  -我们需要医生\N{\r原文字幕}-Tell security!  -We need someone from medical.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.19,0:35:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这里是819号审讯室  -给她解锁\N{\r原文字幕}-Interrogation room 819.  -Uncuff her.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.43,0:35:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马上!\N{\r原文字幕}Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.16,0:35:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪莉怎么说?\N{\r原文字幕}So what did Sherry have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.16,0:35:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她说艾伦心脏病发作\N{\r原文字幕}That Alan had a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.22,0:35:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你相信她吗?\N{\r原文字幕}And you believe her?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.93,0:35:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我相信雪莉为保护自己而说的每一句话 那我就是傻瓜\N{\r原文字幕}I'd be a fool to believe anything Sherry says to save herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.39,0:36:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是 谋杀?\N{\r原文字幕}But murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.24,0:36:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我无法想象她会那样做\N{\r原文字幕}I can't imagine she'd do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.28,0:36:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大卫 在这个关键时刻我们不能被打败\N{\r原文字幕}David, we can't allow ourselves to be caught off guard this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.23,0:36:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须做最坏的设想\N{\r原文字幕}Now we have to assume the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.40,0:36:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么我们也必须设想朱莉娅已经卷入其中\N{\r原文字幕}Then we'd also have to assume that Julia was somehow involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.44,0:36:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么?\N{\r原文字幕}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.57,0:36:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 噢 听我说\N{\r原文字幕}Whoa, whoa, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.91,0:36:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大卫 抱歉 但是朱莉娅和雪莉不一样\N{\r原文字幕}David, I'm sorry, but Julia's not the same kind of person that Sherry is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.65,0:36:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等我们查明了全部真相\N{\r原文字幕}When we find out all the facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.73,0:36:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们再继续讨论这个话题吧\N{\r原文字幕}we'll proceed from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.17,0:36:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还要和杰瑞去查看下早上的基本情况\N{\r原文字幕}I have to go over the morning brief with Jerry.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.95,0:36:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\r原文字幕}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.01,0:36:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-喂?  -朱莉娅 是我\N{\r原文字幕}-Hello?  -Julia, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.65,0:37:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,韦恩?\N{\r原文字幕}Wayne?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.18,0:37:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我刚从艾伦那里听说 我...\N{\r原文字幕}I just heard about Alan, and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.87,0:37:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你一个人吗?\N{\r原文字幕}are you alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.08,0:37:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警察在这里\N{\r原文字幕}The police are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.59,0:37:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警方正要找我谈话\N{\r原文字幕}I'm was just going to speak with one of the officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.98,0:37:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好 告诉我发生什么事了\N{\r原文字幕}All right, tell me what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.69,0:37:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,韦恩 事情发生的时候雪莉在场\N{\r原文字幕}Wayne, Sherry was here when it happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.60,0:37:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是她让我不要告诉警察\N{\r原文字幕}but she told me not to tell the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.51,0:37:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,朱莉娅 我需要你把确切的事情告诉我 好吗?\N{\r原文字幕}Julia, I need for you to tell me exactly what happened over there, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.63,0:37:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们当时在和艾伦说话\N{\r原文字幕}We were talking with Alan.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.78,0:37:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他变得很激动\N{\r原文字幕}He got excited,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.33,0:37:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后他开始喘气\N{\r原文字幕}then he started to gasp for air.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.44,0:37:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他开始心绞痛\N{\r原文字幕}He gets angina.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.03,0:37:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是你打了911 是吗?\N{\r原文字幕}So you called 911, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.78,0:37:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 不是\N{\r原文字幕}No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.34,0:37:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我... 我试图去给他拿药\N{\r原文字幕}I-I tried to give him his medication.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.57,0:37:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你试图?\N{\r原文字幕}What do you mean you tried?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.00,0:37:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪莉阻止了我\N{\r原文字幕}Sherry stopped me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.03,0:37:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去帮艾伦\N{\r原文字幕}I went to help Alan,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.28,0:37:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但她抓住了我的手\N{\r原文字幕}but she grabbed my arm.
